ission grids to competitors.=20
Meanwhile, New York has brought a companion case that says FERC has gone too=
 far and the court should give control of transmission wires back to the sta=
tes.=20
"This is an example of an agency that has overstepped its bounds," Lawrence =
Malone, general counsel for the New York State Public Service Commission, sa=
